  "text": "Apache Kafka enforces log retention policy through a coordinated set of Java source files:\n\nCONFIGURATION AND VALIDATION:\n- `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/config/TopicConfig.java` defines the core configuration constants RETENTION_MS_CONFIG and RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG that specify maximum log retention time and size limits.\n- `server-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/config/ServerLogConfigs.java` defines server-level retention configuration properties including LOG_RETENTION_TIME_MILLIS_CONFIG and LOG_RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG.\n- `storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogConfig.java` implements the main configuration class with three critical validation methods:\n  * `validateRetentionConfigsWhenRemoteCopyDisabled()` (line 539) - validates that local retention settings don't conflict with global retention when remote copy is disabled\n  * `validateRemoteStorageRetentionSize()` (line 578) - validates that local.retention.bytes doesn't exceed retention.bytes\n  * `validateRemoteStorageRetentionTime()` (line 595) - validates that local.retention.ms doesn't exceed retention.ms\n\nSEGMENT DELETION ENFORCEMENT:\n- `storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/UnifiedLog.java` implements the core segment deletion logic:\n  * `deleteOldSegments()` (line 1894) - orchestrates deletion of segments breaching retention policies and log start offset constraints\n  * `deleteRetentionMsBreachedSegments()` (line 1908) - enforces time-based retention (log.retention.ms) by comparing current timestamp with segment's largest timestamp\n  * `deleteRetentionSizeBreachedSegments()` (line 1946) - enforces size-based retention (log.retention.bytes) by deleting segments when total log size exceeds configured limit\n\nRETENTION EXECUTION:\n- `storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleaner.java` calls `deleteOldSegments()` on deletable logs to enforce the retention policies during log cleanup operations.\n\nREMOTE STORAGE RETENTION:\n- `storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/log/remote/storage/RemoteLogManager.java` implements `RemoteLogRetentionHandler` class that extends retention enforcement to remote log segments, supporting both time-based and size-based deletion for tiered storage.\n\nThe retention enforcement follows this chain: LogCleaner -> UnifiedLog.deleteOldSegments() -> deleteRetentionMsBreachedSegments() and deleteRetentionSizeBreachedSegments(), with configuration validation occurring in LogConfig validation methods that ensure local retention settings comply with global retention constraints defined in TopicConfig and ServerLogConfigs."
}

